This paper deals with computer vision tasks related to eye gaze estimation and user understanding, which are typically covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of a large dataset, which could also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
